RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 80. Claiming Purse 16000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BRIGGSEY went to an easy lead to set all the pace throughout, then inched away on the final turn to prove best. HOT TICKET stalked the pace from the two path to the final turn then was asked to make a bid, moving out to three wide in upper stretch and made a late gain on the leader but was not enough. DOMINANT OKIE was off the pace in the two path around the first turn and down the backstretch then was coaxed at the seven sixteenths pole but was empty. PRINCE CAROLINA J tracked the leaders from the inside through the final turn and faded in the stretch drive.

ENTRY.NAME: Briggsey
ENTRY.COMMENT: led throughout, inched away, proved best

ENTRY.NAME: Hot Ticket
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked pace, bid 2w turn, 3w upper, late gain

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 2 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 43. Maiden Claiming Purse 10000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LOCK UP YOUR PETS was off the early pace in the three path then took over at the three eighths pole and drew clear into the stretch and held on for the win. MR GYPSY unseated rider behind the gate, then was roused to make a rail bid into the turn, moving out to three wide in upper stretch and was gaining late on the leader but was only second best. CLEARLY A JET pressed the early pace to the seven sixteenths pole then was taken up to avoid the loose horse going into the turn then made a late stretch run to improve position. SHINE JACK'S DREAM was void of speed and passed tiring rivals. RAINBOW CREST was hustled to the early lead from the inside to the half pole and faded. CAT NAMED HERCULES lost rider after start.

ENTRY.NAME: Clearly a Jet
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed pace, avoid loose horse, late run, improved position

ENTRY.NAME: Lock Up Your Pets
ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace, led 3/8p, drew clear, held on

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 86. Allowance Purse 30000. FOR ACCREDITED OKLAHOMA-BREDS THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (Multiple Winners Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CONNORS OUTLAW pressed the pace from the two path to the top of the stretch then took command and drew off to prove best. DANCING DEVIL tracked the leaders from the three path then was asked at the three eighths pole making a three wide bid, moved out four wide into upper stretch but was not enough to catch the winner. CINCO STEVE was off the pace on the inside then moved out to two wide at the quarter pole but lacked the late response needed. HUNTER QUICK stalked the pace down the backstretch from the four path then moved out to four or five wide in upper stretch but failed to menace. MIRANDEN went to a pressured lead to the quarter pole and gave way grudgingly.

ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace, inside, 2w1/4p, lacked late response,

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 68. Claiming Purse 11000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COZZOLANI was off the pace in the two path then made a three wide bid at the three eighths pole to engage the leader at the three sixteenths pole and dueled to the final sixteenths and drew off. MUSTANGMAGNA pressed the pace from the four path then took the lead at the seven sixteenths pole, was headed at the three sixteenths pole and dueled to the final sixteenth and tired. SCRAPPY PATCH had no early speed then found her stride on the turn moving up from two wide then moved out to four or five wide in upper stretch for a late rally. MISS CANEY tracked the leaders down the backstretch then dropped back going into the stretch and passed tiring rivals. CALI pressed the pace from the two path to the half pole then retreated. GODDESS OF WONDER had good early speed to the turn then vied for the lead around the turn and weakened.

ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace, 3w3/8p, engaged 3/16p, dueled, drew off,

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 6 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 61. Maiden Claiming Purse 10000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 7 1M Dirt CR: 79. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races At A Mile Or Over Since January 4 Allowed 3 lbs. Such A Race Since Then Allowed 6 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Races Where Entered For $4 ,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KIMBELL'S STRATEGY was allowed to settle to the three furlong pole then was coaxed and made a three wide bid on the final turn and moved out to four wide in upper stretch for a late run and engaged the leader at the eighth pole and drew clear. STAYTHIRSTYMYAMIGO hopped at the start spotting the field many lengths and trailed to the three furlong pole, launched a two wide bid around the final turn, moved between horses at the three sixteenths pole to be a clear second. C C THE BARTENDER stalked the pace from the off the rail around the first turn then made a two wide bid at the five furlong pole and took the lead at the quarter pole, was headed at the eighth pole and weakened. STRONG WOMAN tracked the leaders from the four path through the final turn then moved out to five or six wide in upper stretch but didn't make a bid. FAVORITE SISTER was unhurried through the final turn and passed tiring rivals. SHE'S A PLAYER had the unchallenged lead for three quarters and tired. WIREWIREWIRE was off the pace in the three path to the quarter pole and gave way.

ENTRY.NAME: Kimbell's Strategy
ENTRY.COMMENT: allowed to settle, coaxed 3/8p, 4wupper, engaged1/8p, cleared

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 8 1M Dirt CR: 91. Claiming Purse 18000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HAPPY ROMANCE was off the pace around the first turn and down the backstretch then was asked at the three furlong pole and moved up to engage the leader at the eighth pole and was able to clear late. KWONTRO went to a clear lead to the eighth pole then was headed and fought gamely but gave way grudgingly. RACE DAY REBAL stalked the pace from the three path to the final turn then made a three wide mild bid and was the best of the rest. INCA EMPIRE was unhurried through the final turn and passed tiring rivals. AQUIMINE was allowed to settle around the first turn then made a mild middle move through the turn and weakened. BIG SKIPPER raced near the back and was never a factor. SWEET BAKER was close up on the pace in the two path to the three furlong pole and gave way.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 9 6F Dirt CR: 69. Maiden Special Weight Purse 21000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GOSPEL SISTER was rushed to the lead, was headed at the quarter pole but came again and won going away. EURA NORTHERN SKY broke well then was allowed to settle down the backstretch, was coaxed at the half pole moving up on the inside and made a late run to be up for second. DODGEBALL pressed the pace from the two path through the turn then engaged the leader at the quarter pole but was empty in the stretch drive. OKIE CODE raced in the middle of the pack on the inside down the backstretch then moved out to three wide on the turn and was outkicked in the stretch drive. RUN DOTTIE RUN raced in the middle of the pack from the three path but was never a factor. OKIE HOPE raced near the back on the inside and was never a threat. O S U BUDKE raced in the middle of the pack in the two path to the three furlong pole then dropped back.

ENTRY.NAME: Gospel Sister
ENTRY.COMMENT: rushed to lead, headed 1/4p, came again, going away

ENTRY.NAME: Eura Northern Sky
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke well, allowed to settle, coaxed 1/2p, late run for 2nd
